Dianne Clinton on Instagram: “Although I have yet to meet Stella in person, her parents Sarah and Myles share their lives through social media and I feel like Stella and I would be great friends if we knew each other 😊. She has had, and will continue to have, many challenges. In addition to having regular everyday issues that we all have, Stella and her family endure much more. They conquer every challenge with smiles and positivity and I see that Stella is a huge contributor to this family attitude. She is full of happiness, laughter, dance moves, singing, artwork, and positivity. Fun nail polish, brightly coloured artwork, hot tubs, pop music, and her cute little brother are just a few things she focuses on enjoying every day. Stella does not let SMA hold her back from anything she wants to do. I value this outlook and will continue to contribute to her life when I can. I sell these star ornaments to help with their added costs. Stella needs a special bathroom to streamline her life. These star ornaments are $5 and every star sold gets Stella a small $5 step closer to having the washroom facilities she needs at home. These stars are great to top gifts, they are kid-friendly for decorating during the holiday season, and are a lovely reminder that you helped a little girl shine brighter. Place your orders people! While supplies last! #nevergiveup”
